President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to appoint several individuals to key positions in his administration. These appointments include:
- Pamella DeVos, Robert Castellani, Brian D. Ballard, and Mary Helen Bowers as Members of the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts.
- David Marchick, Jeffrey Miller, Adam S. Boehler, Jimmy Resnick, and Daniel Huff as Members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council.
- Heidi H. Stirrup and Wes Spurlock as Members of the Board of Visitors to the United States Air Force Academy.
- John Coale as a Member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Naval Academy.
- Eugene R. Lutz as a Member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Merchant Marine Academy.
- Professor Steve H. Hanke and Dale Ahlquist as Members of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences.
- Thomas Emanuel Dans and Crawford Patkotak as Members of the Arctic Research Commission.
- Robert Benedict Bowes as a Member of the Community Development Advisory Board.
- Garrick Davis as a Member of the Board of Trustees of the American Folklife Center.
- Yesli Vega as a Member of the President's Advisory Commission on Hispanic Prosperity.
- Marcia Lee Kelly as a Member of the Committee for the Preservation of the White House.
- Brian H. Hook as a Member of the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars in the Smithsonian Institution.
- Ray W. Washburne as a Member of the National Security Education Board.
- David R. Legates as a Member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science.